<subSubSection id="F6A765130232CF172ABEFDB3E039F8A7" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BE0236980232CF172ABEFDB3E039F8A7" blockId="2.[151,1437,549,1907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172ABEFDB3E05BF81F" bold="true" box="[151,280,549,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B00FDB3E0AAF81F" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[297,489,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B00FDB3E0AAF81F" box="[297,489,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Masculine gender. The genus name recognizes Eric van den Berghe, Director of Biodiversity and Associate Professor of Ecology, Zamorano University, 
<collectingCountry id="C6AA76080232CF1729E4FDDFE57EF843" box="[973,1085,585,611]" name="Honduras" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, for his dedicated fieldwork in zoology and botany.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6A765130232CF172AEEFD07E234F88B" box="[199,887,656,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="BE0236980232CF172AEEFD07E234F88B" blockId="2.[151,1437,549,1907]" box="[199,887,656,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172AEEFD07E018F88B" bold="true" box="[199,347,656,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<typeStatus id="6106883A0232CF172AEEFD07E041F88B" box="[199,258,657,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B40FD07E3F0F88B" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[361,691,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celaquensis">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B40FD07E3F0F88B" box="[361,691,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius celaquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, here designated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6A765130232CF172AEEFD22E1FAFF2F" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" type="description">
<paragraph id="BE0236980232CF172AEEFD22E1FAFF2F" blockId="2.[151,1437,549,1907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172AEEFD22E012F8EF" bold="true" box="[199,337,692,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Description</emphasis>
. Small size, cylindrical. Head not retractile; frons transverse; antennal tubercles moderately elevat- ed, distinctly separate from each other basally; palpi slender, unequal, with apical segments pointed; eyes coarsely faceted, not divided; upper eye lobes well-separate; lower eye lobes about as long as gena; antennae slender, 11- segmented, distinctly longer than body; scape moderately short, wide, fusiform, without apical cicatrix; antennomere III distinctly longer than scape, shorter than IV; antennomeres gradually decreasing in length from V to XI. Prothorax slightly transverse, with posterior constriction well-marked; sides slightly rounded anteriorly, widely, distinctly rounded from before middle to posterior constriction. Pronotum with large, strongly elevated, nearly conical tubercle on each side, from anterior quarter to after middle, and another tubercle centrally, distinctly less elevated, placed from posterior constriction to about middle. Prosternal process moderately narrowed centrally. Procoxal cavities closed posteriorly. Elytra gradually narrowed from base to apex, more strongly from posterior quarter; with distinct centrobasal crest in anterior quarter, with top inclined toward outer side; with three moderately well-marked carinae dorsally, from centrobasal crest to near apex; apex almost truncate, unarmed; without isolated erect setae. Pro- and mesofemora clavate; metafemora pedunculate-clavate. Protibiae slightly, gradually widened from base to apex; mesotibiae strongly sulcate dorsally; metatibiae slightly depressed dorsally in posterior third, and with fringe of thick, short, erect setae in this area. Pro- and mesotarsi slightly longer than tibia; metatarsi about as long as tibia; metatarsomere I shorter than II–III together. Abdominal ventrite I longest, II–IV subequal in length, V longer than IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6A765130232CF172AEEFA8FE454FD53" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BE0236980232CF172AEEFA8FE454FD53" blockId="2.[151,1437,549,1907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172AEEFA8FE077FF13" bold="true" box="[199,308,1305,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Remarks</emphasis>
. Following the key to genera of 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1728B7FA8FE275FF13" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[670,822,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Apomecynini">Apomecynini</taxonomicName>
from 
<bibRefCitation id="DA2C4B690232CF172952FA8FE50BFF13" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[891,1096,1305,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" pagination="411 - 930" refId="ref9124" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. (1872) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Genera des Coleopteres, ou expose methodique et critique de tous les genres proposes jusqu'ici dans cet ordre d'insectes. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 9 (2), 411 - 930." type="journal article" year="1872">Lacordaire (1872)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172E7AFA8FE450FF13" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[1107,1299,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172E7AFA8FE450FF13" box="[1107,1299,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172F33FA8FE4C0FF13" bold="true" box="[1306,1411,1305,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="97FA57F10232CF172F33FA8FE4C0FF13" box="[1306,1411,1305,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B20FAA8E318FF77" authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[265,603,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mycerinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B20FAA8E0E3FF77" box="[265,416,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Mycerinopsis</emphasis>
Thomson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
, a genus distributed in the Australian zoogeographical region. However, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B0DFAF4E0F8FF5B" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[292,443,1378,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mycerinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B0DFAF4E0F8FF5B" box="[292,443,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Mycerinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pronotum distinctly tuberculate (not tuberculate in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172E6EFAF4E59DFF5B" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[1095,1246,1378,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mycerinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172E6EFAF4E59DFF5B" box="[1095,1246,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Mycerinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and elytra with centrobasal crest (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172BF8FA10E32BFFBF" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[465,616,1414,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mycerinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172BF8FA10E32BFFBF" box="[465,616,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Mycerinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Following the key to genera of American 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172E7FFA13E5ADFFBF" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[1110,1262,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Apomecynini">Apomecynini</taxonomicName>
from 
<bibRefCitation id="DA2C4B690232CF172F1DFA13E1A6FFE3" author="Breuning, S." pageId="2" pageNumber="563" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref8875" refString="Breuning, S. (1971) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Abhandlungen und Berichte aus dem staatlichen Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172AC6FA3FE0ECFFE3" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[239,431,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172AC6FA3FE0ECFFE3" box="[239,431,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B9CFA3FE35EFFE3" bold="true" box="[437,541,1449,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="97FA57F10232CF172B9CFA3FE35EFFE3" box="[437,541,1449,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
lies with 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1728A0FA3FE29BFFE3" authority="Breuning, 1943" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1943" box="[649,984,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tucumaniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF1728A0FA3FE262FFE3" box="[649,801,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Tucumaniella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DA2C4B690232CF17290EFA3FE29BFFE3" author="Breuning, S." box="[807,984,1449,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" pagination="12 - 66" refId="ref8809" refString="Breuning, S. (1943) Novae species Cerambycidarum. XII. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 12, 12 - 66." type="journal article" year="1943">Breuning, 1943</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="DA2C4B690232CF172ECCFA3FE4D4FFE3" author="Breuning, S." box="[1253,1431,1449,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" pagination="12 - 66" refId="ref8809" refString="Breuning, S. (1943) Novae species Cerambycidarum. XII. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 12, 12 - 66." type="journal article" year="1943">Breuning (1943</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DA2C4B690232CF172ABEFA5BE191FFC7" author="Breuning, S." box="[151,210,1485,1511]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref8875" refString="Breuning, S. (1971) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Abhandlungen und Berichte aus dem staatlichen Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
), the scape in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B57FA5BE355FFC7" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1943" box="[382,534,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tucumaniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B57FA5BE355FFC7" box="[382,534,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Tucumaniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very long (short in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172908FA5BE2A2FFC7" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[801,993,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172908FA5BE2A2FFC7" box="[801,993,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennomere III slightly longer than scape (distinctly longer in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172BE8FA67E3C2FC2B" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[449,641,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172BE8FA67E3C2FC2B" box="[449,641,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennal tubercles forming lobe at apex (not so in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172EE5FA67E4CFFC2B" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[1228,1420,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172EE5FA67E4CFFC2B" box="[1228,1420,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), prothorax with sides nearly straight (not so in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1728BFF983E215FC0F" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[662,854,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF1728BFF983E215FC0F" box="[662,854,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and pronotum with three transverse and deep sulci (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172B27F9AFE08DFC73" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[270,462,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172B27F9AFE08DFC73" box="[270,462,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It slightly resembles 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1728FBF9AFE523FC73" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 2008" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2008" box="[722,1120,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Irundiaba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF1728FBF9AFE201FC73" box="[722,834,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Irundiaba</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 2008
</taxonomicName>
by the prothoracic and pronotal shape, and by the presence of a centrobasal crest. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1729B3F9CBE549FC57" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2008" box="[922,1034,1629,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Irundiaba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF1729B3F9CBE549FC57" box="[922,1034,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Irundiaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lower eye lobes are longer than gena (about as long in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172BBEF917E314FCBB" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[407,599,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172BBEF917E314FCBB" box="[407,599,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennomere III longer than IV (shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172E66F917E44CFCBB" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[1103,1295,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172E66F917E44CFCBB" box="[1103,1295,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), outer apex of the elytra projected (rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172834F933E39EFC9F" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[541,733,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172834F933E39EFC9F" box="[541,733,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and tarsomere V longer than I–III together (distinctly shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172A9DF95FE037FCC3" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero, 2019" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2019" box="[180,372,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vandenbergheius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172A9DF95FE037FCC3" box="[180,372,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Vandenbergheius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The general appearance is also similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172981F95FE5B8FCC3" authority="Breuning, 1940" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[936,1275,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paraesylacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172981F95FE507FCC3" box="[936,1092,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Paraesylacris</emphasis>
Breuning, 1940
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the absence of erect setae on the elytra (present in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF1728E6F97BE228FD27" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[719,875,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paraesylacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF1728E6F97BE228FD27" box="[719,875,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Paraesylacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), scape fusiform (gradually widened basally, then nearly parallel-sided toward apex in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172805F887E38BFD0B" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[556,712,1809,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paraesylacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172805F887E38BFD0B" box="[556,712,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Paraesylacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and upper eye lobes distinctly separated from each other (upper eye lobes separated by distance shorter than width of one lobe in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF17294FF8A3E541FD6F" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[870,1026,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paraesylacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF17294FF8A3E541FD6F" box="[870,1026,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Paraesylacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Finally, the new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172ABEF8CFE083FD53" authority="Thomson, 1868" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,448,1881,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethystola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172ABEF8CFE04AFD53" box="[151,265,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Tethystola</emphasis>
Thomson, 1868
</taxonomicName>
especially by the absence of erect setae on the elytra (present in 
<taxonomicName id="79BD4D1B0232CF172EBCF8CFE444FD53" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1173,1287,1881,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethystola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC9EA8A0232CF172EBCF8CFE444FD53" box="[1173,1287,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Tethystola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
